Policy data:
- Type: {{ policy.type }}
- Coverage: {{ policy.coverage }}
- Location: {{ policy.location }}
- Risk: {{ policy.risk }}

Optional document context:
{% if chunks %}
{% for chunk in chunks %}
[{{ chunk.context_label }}]
[Source {{ loop.index }}] {{ chunk.document_name }}, section {{ chunk.chunk_index + 1 }}, score {{ "%.3f"|format(chunk.score) }}
{{ chunk.content }}

{% endfor %}
{% else %}
No document context was provided.
{% endif %}

Return JSON with exactly these fields:
- summary: a concise operational summary of the policy.
- risk_analysis: practical underwriting or review risks based on the policy data and supplied document context.
- email: a complete client-ready email, not an email address. It must include:
  - a subject line
  - greeting
  - short policy summary
  - key coverage/risk notes
  - recommended next steps
  - professional closing

Do not put only a recipient address in the email field. If a recipient address appears in context, use it only inside the email body when appropriate.
